  "response": "To build muscle with calisthenics, try these strategies:\n\n1. Progressive Overload\n- Increase repetitions\n- Add difficulty to exercises\n- Use more challenging variations\n- Slow down movement tempo\n\n2. Key Muscle-Building Exercises\n- Push-ups (chest, triceps)\n- Pull-ups (back, biceps)\n- Dips (chest, triceps)\n- Squats (legs)\n- Lunges\n- Planks\n- Burpees\n- Handstand push-ups\n\n3. Training Techniques\n- High-volume sets (8-12 reps)\n- Multiple sets per exercise\n- Short rest periods\n- Training to muscle failure\n- Compound movements\n\n4. Advanced Variations\n- One-arm push-ups\n- Muscle-ups\n- Pistol squats\n- Planche progressions\n- Front/back levers\n\n5. Nutrition Tips\n- Increase protein intake\n- Eat in a slight caloric surplus\n- Consume complex carbohydrates\n- Stay hydrated\n- Consider protein supplements\n\n6. Rest and Recovery\n- Get adequate sleep\n- Allow muscle recovery time\n- Stretch and mobilize\n- Manage stress\n\nConsistency and proper progression are key to muscle growth with calisthenics.",
